<br>
&quot;I feel at this time ever so much more angry than I had been the evening before when I finally came about to responding to Aailin's mudslinging comments!  Despite claims that he wished to keep the buisness spoken of private, he put up his words in a public forum for all to see and they were left untouched for three days, giving even more people to come and read.  When I felt I had allowed myself to calm as much as I possibly could, I responded to his accusations, only to awake today and find the entire conversation torn down and destroyed.<br>
<br>
I will NOT allow myself to be attacked in a public room in the way I was and not come to my defense.  I will NOT sit at home and watch one say such filthy things about me and do nothing.  If you will tear down my note where I would have prefered to leave it, I will simply go beyond your authority.  I had figured someone would take that course of action, so I made copies of the notes before hand.<br>
<br>
If you wish to know why this is now out in the open, please ask the two officers involved.  I do not allow somebody to spit in my face and when I attempt to slap him in return, have his friends come out and hold me down. Still, I have strong feelings that I will alienate further people with what I have to say, but feel I must regardless as I will not be treated like dirty garbage.  I suppose the difference would be between those who accually ever cared for myself as an individual, and those who only saw me as an enchanter, just another member, an object to be used toward an end.<br>
<br>
Three days ago, I put up a discussion to say my goodbyes to Resolution in their public room.  I wanted all to know that I had withdrawn my application to their rivals, and had instead decided to retire from adventures forever.  This message was calm and not the one in question.  In my farewell to Resolution in the private rooms however, the one put up when I was only leaving the guild, was quite long and details my feelings and frustrations and emotions for why I was leaving the guild.  The words were often blunt and directly to the point, but they were the truth as told through my feelings, and something I felt everyone in Resolution deserved to know, so there were no questions or feelings of uncertainty left behind.  My words were not evil nor insulting to individuals, all of whom I still care for deeply, but they were the bare truth of my feelings toward the institution of Resolution.<br>
<br>
Before all these words are read, I will again offer my deepest apoligies to all the people who I will always consider my friends, and who may be shocked or disappointed in my choice of action.  I do not do this in an attempt to smear the name of Resolution, and I will remind ALL others who read this that I am obviously angry now at one specific person and his words.  I have grown frustrated to the verge of tears over this matter several times over and cannot allow it to simply go away as it had.  These frustrations are a large portion of why I eventually decided to leave your mortal lands forever, and I do not care to have them tugging and eatting at my heart still in the brief retirement before my final days.<br>
<br>
In my public goodbye, Aailin, who was made an officer of Resolution in my final few days, left this in plain view of ALL passing eyes:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>*a copy of a note is attached, complete with a secondhand signature*</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>'/removes his officer hat<br>
<br>
<br>
You know Ayri I was going to post this on the FV soapbox.<br>
But it isn't anyone's concern really. It was between Resolution and you.<br>
<br>
Well you see Ayrielle this is something that has been eating at me for a while.<br>
<br>
