<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>*a second copy of a note is attached*</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  The following are my words in responce:<br>
<br>
*stomps her feet furiously!* &gt;=\ <br>
<br>
*posts up a lengthy note, torn in a few places by the pen, apparently from writing too hard:*<br>
<br>
&quot;I have given this note much time.  I had at first been furious at what I read, and then decided to take the advice I so often gave others, and allowed myself to calm down before answering any attacks upon my person.  I relaxed for a time, then came back and found myself furious still, so I relaxed longer.<br>
<br>
Now I come back as furious as ever!  Each time I read the words accusing myself of being a horrible person I grow even more furious!  If your goal was to see what I am truly like when angry and volatile, you have chosen the best of paths because my following statements will likely dwarf those written in the farewell that you speak of!  I have retired from adventures due in part to frustrations such as this only to find they do not yet go away!  If anything have become stronger!<br>
<br>
I am accused of being a liar bent on destruction and harm to those I called my friends, and then damned to a terrible fate in closing!  I am told I am egotistical and dismissed like unwanted garbage! <br>
<br>
I am a good person, and I have little room within my soul for anything but kindness, but I can only take and put up with so much!  You have managed to dance upon this imaginary boundary at times before, but now you have done well to step full across!  I am NOT one to be pushed around, bullied, manipulated, nor cornered, and I am THROUGH tolerating such behavior!<br>
<br>
When I left Resolution I did in fact leave a lengthy note behind.  This note was full of things that I knew would make some people feel bad and perhaps guilty, but I left that note for a good reason, and that reason was not to bring about depression and hurt feelings!  <br>
<br>
I left the note because I felt, and still DO feel, that Resolution deserved to know why.  Leaving in silence was not an option for myself because that option would lead nowhere for the betterment of the guild nor its morale, nor myself!  Should I have simply slipped out the door when no one was looking, leaving people do find out when they see my application elsewhere?  Should I leave everyone to start rumors and make crazy assumptions about my motivation, so that I can become a power-mongering, treasure whore?  Maybe a despicable traitor, run off to Fire and Fury to sell my secrets?  Do not tell myself that this would not happen.  It DID happen with the people who had left just before!  Do not tell me they were not spoken poorly of in their absence when you know for undeniable truth that they were! <br>
<br>
I thought it best that everyone hear directly from myself my reasons for the building frustration and my eventual leaving.  Yes, those words were perhaps harsh and blunt, but they were my feelings.  Did you already forget the large note I left up earlier?  The one stating that I would no longer sit by and watch our problems mount upon themselves?  The one that stated I would begin to take the form of a stronger leader of people, and that I would soon come to speak harshly when harsh words were needed?  The one that I left for all to see two full weeks before these incidents?!  Why do you act surprised when I followed through?<br>
<br>
My statements in the farewell were an insight into at least one person's frustrations and reason for leaving the guild.  Since the time they were written they have been supported by the explanations that I have heard of why other people left!  Maybe, instead of claiming I am an evil seductress that spits lies and venom, you could take your head out of the proverbial sand and see the obvious that stands right before you, despite your attempts to push blame upon a scapegoat!<br>
<br>
Perhaps I spoke with assuredness behind my words, not because I was egotistical and oh-so-perfect, but because my points were based upon valid observations that I had made over an extended period of time, and the facts and circumstances surrounding the situations strongly support what I had to say!!  Funny how so many who once claimed myself to be wise and knowledgeable in my words so quickly change their opinion when I speak something that is difficult to hear. <br>
<br>
Why are others to be forgiven and welcomed to open arms should they wish to return and I am not?  Because I had the courage and the sense of responsibility to the guild (even in my farewell to all I must add) to point out the blatantly obvious for all to see, but that most had previously blinded themselves to?  &gt;=\<br>
<br>
Do you have any idea how hard I had worked upon solving these problems long before?  Do you have any idea how many times I had to harp upon detail after detail after detail only to be either ignored or pushed off until a later that does not ever come?   Do you have any idea what it feels like to put forth so much effort into solving something that people want fixed, but no one wishes to help fix?!  Do you have any idea what it is like to have a choice of two options, both of which will make happy half of the people while angering the other half, and still try to find that middle ground for all?!<br>
<br>
The more I write these words with my pen the more furious I become!  I am to have my thoughts, feelings, and words toward the inanimate institution of Resolution and have them turn into a personal hatred and disgust for myself?!  I have never wished anything but the most attainable happiness possible for the individuals for Resolution, and even though some very clearly do not care for myself, I still wish good for all.  But I did not insult anyone!<br>
<br>
Yes, I do feel like Resolution was no longer living up to what I had wanted and expected when I first applied!  Yes, I did point out many of the reasons for such a failure!  You speak as if you would prefer to remain ignorant so that you can dance upon your merry way toward the cliff without realizing it is there!  WHY NOT TAKE THE OPPORTUNITY TO ADDRESS THESE NOW RECOGNIZED ISSUES AND WORK TOWARD SOLVING THEM TOGETHER?!  Keeping your eyes closed will do NOTHING, and I will repeat forcefully again, NOTHING!!!, to help!  It simply means you will be made to endure the same problems over and over again!  Is this what you want?  Is this what everyone cares to strive for?<br>
<br>
I cannot yet contain the frustration I feel, and it now strikes myself with three times the power it had when I had decided that I felt too much and left!  I cannot get over the thought that an officer (take off your hat all you like, you will represent the guild with every word you utter while serving as an officer) has gone to such lengths as to use petty tactics that you so often accused those who you hate most for using!  Your implications are that I purposely came forth with the intent to harm and endanger Resolution, and that I have been a terrible person from the very start only playing at being nice so that I can seep inside to bring about more powerful destruction!  These words have no basis in fact and can only be supported by your irrational assumptions that have obviously been poorly jumped to in yet another fit of enraged hysterics DESPITE MY TWICE COMING TO YOU IN THE PAST AND ENCOURAGING YOU TO RECONSIDER SUCH ACTIONS!!  What you end up with is an abhorrent use of propaganda aimed negatively in my direction that serves no logical purpose and ends up, in this case ironically, turning you into the malicious one that you accuse me of being!  Perhaps when I awaken next I will find myself accused of selling all those missing items for platinum that I worked hard to locate for people, so I can support my wild addiction to Misty Thicket Picnics, or that I single-handedly engineered and led the mass-exodus from Resolution! <br>
<br>
Why begin a battle that you can hope to gain nothing from?  Why push she whom you are attacking into a place from which she feels she must fight back or risk LOSING something?!  Did you not see the folly in giving myself the option to defend myself in full view of the public or to fall over and endure a verbal thrashing that I do not feel is justified in the least?!  Why, if you wished this to remain private between Resolution and myself do you put up your words in a public forum for all who pass through to see?!  Do you understand nothing of emotions or tactics?  Did you not see where this would lead to?!  Why do you think I had twice before come to you as a friend and tried to help you avoid these situations and how to better conduct yourself in public?!  The second time during which you decided it would be better to continue upon the path and turn THAT attempt at friendship and caring into a fight!<br>
<br>
You have morphed since being awarded the badge of officer.  You remain the same person as before, except what is referred to as the corruption of power has gone to your head, and you are now infinitely more arrogant and stubborn than ever before, despite situations in which OVERWHELMING EVIDENCE slaps you in the face!  The few days in which we served as officers together were very much the final frustrations that pushed myself over the edge of tolerance, since none could have a conversation with you that did not result in your primitive display of pompous chest-pounding and insistence that you know what is best no matter what anyone else says.  As goes with the advice that I left to the leadership stated, that a leader can be wrong but never unsure, and I knew that the future would hold nothing but head-butting and disagreeance, a strong form of unreliability.  If you cannot handle the responsibility that comes with being a leader, I suggest that you turn the title over to someone who can.<br>
<br>
I do not write these words because I want to hurt you or Resolution.  I write them because I am sick of dealing with this time and again and even in retirement yet.  If you ever wished to know what an enraged Ayrielle would be like, here is your desire. <br>
<br>
&gt;=\<br>
<br>
But do not fear, even though I am angry with you, I will continue to forgive yourself for the wrongs I feel you have done to me because, despite your claims to the contrary and what emotions that did explode here, I believe myself to be a very kind person at heart.'<br>
<br>
